:"about 1376–12 November 1408","1376–1408":"1376–1408","1374–1435":"1374–1435","1405–1422":"1405–1422","1355–1388":"1355–1388","1368–1388":"1368–1388","1374":"1374","before 1405":"before 1405","1435":"1435","1368":"1368","1422":"1422","1388":"1388","1355":"1355","1376":"1376","about 1376":"about 1376","1408":"1408","after 1388":"after 1388","12 November 1408":"12 November 1408","1405":"1405","Sheepham, Modbury Parish, Devon, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","Norries, Devonshire, England":"Devon, England, United Kingdom","North Huish, Devonshire, England":"North Huish, Devon, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Norreys","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Norris  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Norris","meanings":["English:","habitational name from Middle English <i>norreis</i>, <i>noreis</i>, <i>norais</i> ‘northerner’ (Anglo-Norman French <i>noreis</i>), used both of Norwegians and of inhabitants of northern England and Scotland.","from the Middle English personal name <i>Norreis</i>, derived from <i>norreis</i> ‘northerner’."]}]},{"name":"Eleanor","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ellenor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor  , the result of blending with   Ellen ."]},{"name":"Elenor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]},{"name":"Elinor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eleanor Norreys was born about 1376, in North Huish, Devon, England, United Kingdom, her father, William Norreys, was 23 and her mother, Eleanor de Collaton, was 10. She married John Fortescue before 1405. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died on 12 November 1408, at the age of 33."},"et":{"about 1376–12 November 1408":"umbes 1376–12. november 1408","1376–1408":"1376–1408","1374–1435":"1374–1435","1405–1422":"1405–1422","1355–1388":"1355–1388","1368–1388":"1368–1388","1374":"1374","before 1405":"enne 1405","1435":"1435","1368":"1368","1422":"1422","1388":"1388","1355":"1355","1376":"1376","about 1376":"umbes 1376","1408":"1408","after 1388":"pärast 1388","12 November 1408":"12. november 1408","1405":"1405","Sheepham, Modbury Parish, Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norries, Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","North Huish, Devonshire, England":"North Huish, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1376–12 November 1408":"noin 1376–12. marraskuuta 1408","1376–1408":"1376–1408","1374–1435":"1374–1435","1405–1422":"1405–1422","1355–1388":"1355–1388","1368–1388":"1368–1388","1374":"1374","before 1405":"ennen vuotta 1405","1435":"1435","1368":"1368","1422":"1422","1388":"1388","1355":"1355","1376":"1376","about 1376":"noin 1376","1408":"1408","after 1388":"1388 jälkeen","12 November 1408":"12. marraskuuta 1408","140